TY  - JOUR
AU  - Martell, Rodolfo
T1  - Understanding Common Factors in Domestic and International Bond Spreads*
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfn004
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 12
IS  - 2
SP  - 365
EP  - 389
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - I study the determinants of changes in credit spreads for U.S. dollar denominated domestic and foreign sovereign bonds using fundamentals specified by structural models to separate spreads into their credit and non-credit components. I find that the non-default portions of spreads have a component that is common for each type of debt. Further, using a vector autoregressive model, I find that domestic spreads are related to the lagged component of sovereign spreads. I also find that some proxies for liquidity are related to the common components, suggesting a liquidity-based explanation for the common component not identified by previous research.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfn004
ER  - 



